  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Clinic Assistant",
  "description": "<ul><li>Have an opportunity to join a fast growing healthcare group with career progression.</li><li>Hiring senior clinic assistant with at least 1-2 years of GP clinic work experience.</li></ul><p>To assist in the daily operations of the clinic inclusive but not limited to the following:</p><p><u><strong>Counter duties:</strong></u><br />- Registration of patients, triage taking<br />- Dispensing of medication, closing payment, and collection of outstanding payments<br />- Assist in booking of appointment for patients for chronic disease and remind patients of their upcoming appointments<br />- Refill and top up medications<br />- Administrative tasks<br />- Submission of claims eg Medisave, CHAS, MBS and Managed Care claims for different insurance schemes.<br /></p><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u><br />- Ability to work in a fast paced environment<br />- Diligent and willing to learn<br />- Good command of spoken and written English<br />- Good IT proficiency required (Computer system, Managed Care portals)<br />- Familiar with MBS, MHCP claim portal.<br />- Familiar with TPA claims.<br />- Minimum GCE O level and above with relevant experience in healthcare/ GP clinic setting.<br />- Customer service orientation with pleasant disposition.<br />- Experience in GP clinic is necessary.<br />- Ability to speak Mandarin and/or Malay will be an advantage, in order to communicate with and dispense medications to Chinese and Malay speaking patients who are unable to speak English<br />- Able to work shifts - 44 hours/ week, inclusive of 3 nights and 1 weekend<br /><br />Full time employment benefits including CPF and 13th month<br />Interested applicants please email to ourwestcoastfamilyclinic@gmail.com</p>",
